+# Modular Rust Architecture
+
+## Overview
+
+The Rust codebase has been restructured from a monolithic single-crate design into a modular multi-crate workspace. This improves maintainability, testability, and enables focused benchmarking of individual components.
+
+## Previous Structure
+
+```
+rust/
+└── worker/
+    ├── src/
+    │   ├── types/
+    │   ├── distance/
+    │   ├── blockstore/
+    │   ├── system/
+    │   ├── index/
+    │   ├── execution/
+    │   ├── compactor/
+    │   ├── server/
+    │   └── ... (other modules)
+    └── Cargo.toml
+```
+
+All code was in a single `worker` crate, making it difficult to:
+- Test individual modules in isolation
+- Benchmark specific components
+- Understand dependency relationships
+- Reuse code across different services
+
+## New Structure
+
+```
+rust/
+├── chroma-proto/       # Protocol buffer definitions
+├── chroma-types/       # Core domain types
+├── chroma-distance/    # Distance metric implementations
+├── chroma-blockstore/  # Block storage abstractions
+├── chroma-system/      # Actor system framework
+├── chroma-index/       # Indexing implementations
+└── worker/             # Application binary
+```
+
+## Crate Details
+
+### chroma-proto
+**Purpose**: Protocol buffer definitions
+**Dependencies**: tonic, prost
+**Exports**: Generated protobuf types for Chroma API
+
+Independent crate containing all protocol buffer definitions. This allows other crates to depend on API types without requiring the full worker implementation.
+
+### chroma-types
+**Purpose**: Core domain types
+**Dependencies**: chroma-proto, uuid, serde, thiserror
+**Exports**:
+- Collection, Segment, Record types
+- Metadata and operation types
+- Error definitions
+- Flush and tenant types
+
+Foundation crate that defines the core domain model. All other crates depend on these types.
+
+### chroma-distance
+**Purpose**: Distance metric calculations
+**Dependencies**: thiserror
+**Exports**:
+- DistanceFunction enum (Euclidean, Cosine, InnerProduct)
+- SIMD-optimized implementations (SSE, AVX, NEON)
+
+**Benchmarks**: `benches/distance_metrics.rs`
+
+Pure computational crate with no external service dependencies. Can be benchmarked and tested independently.
+
+### chroma-blockstore
+**Purpose**: Block storage abstractions
+**Dependencies**: chroma-types, arrow, roaring, parking_lot, foyer
+**Exports**:
+- BlockfileProvider trait
+- Arrow-based implementation
+- Memory-based implementation
+- Sparse index utilities
+
+**Benchmarks**: `benches/blockstore_bench.rs`
+
+Handles persistent and in-memory block storage. Isolated from higher-level query logic.
+
+### chroma-system
+**Purpose**: Actor system and execution framework
+**Dependencies**: chroma-types, tokio, futures
+**Exports**:
+- System, Component traits
+- Executor and scheduler
+- Message passing infrastructure
+
+Provides the runtime system for asynchronous component execution. Can be tested with different component implementations.
+
+### chroma-index
+**Purpose**: Index implementations
+**Dependencies**: chroma-types, chroma-blockstore, chroma-distance, tantivy, roaring
+**Exports**:
+- HNSW index for vector search
+- Full-text search indices
+- Metadata filtering
+
+**Build Requirements**: Requires hnswlib C++ library (via build.rs)
+
+Encapsulates all indexing logic. Dependencies on distance and blockstore are explicit.
+
+### worker
+**Purpose**: Main application binary
+**Dependencies**: All chroma-* crates + service infrastructure
+**Binaries**:
+- query_service
+- compaction_service
+
+Thin orchestration layer that composes library crates into running services. Contains minimal business logic.
+
+## Dependency Graph
+
+```
+                    ┌─────────────┐
+                    │ chroma-proto│
+                    └──────┬──────┘
+                           │
+                    ┌──────▼──────┐
+                    │ chroma-types│◄────────┐
+                    └──────┬──────┘         │
+                           │                │
+          ┌────────────────┼─────────┐      │
+          │                │         │      │
+   ┌──────▼──────┐  ┌──────▼─────┐  │      │
+   │chroma-      │  │chroma-     │  │      │
+   │distance     │  │blockstore  │  │      │
+   └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬─────┘  │      │
+          │                │         │      │
+          └────────────────┼─────────┤      │
+                           │         │      │
+                    ┌──────▼─────┐   │      │
+                    │chroma-     │   │      │
+                    │system      │   │      │
+                    └──────┬─────┘   │      │
+                           │         │      │
+                           └─────────┼──────┤
+                                     │      │
+                              ┌──────▼──────▼──┐
+                              │ chroma-index   │
+                              └──────┬─────────┘
+                                     │
+                              ┌──────▼─────┐
+                              │   worker   │
+                              └────────────┘
+```
+
+## Benefits
+
+### 1. Clear Dependency Boundaries
+Each crate explicitly declares its dependencies in `Cargo.toml`. This makes architectural decisions visible and prevents circular dependencies.
+
+**Example**: chroma-distance has no dependencies on storage or system modules, making it truly reusable.
+
+### 2. Focused Testing
+Tests can be run for individual crates without compiling the entire codebase.
+
+```bash
+# Test only distance calculations
+cargo test -p chroma-distance
+
+# Test only types
+cargo test -p chroma-types
+```
+
+### 3. Independent Benchmarking
+Each crate can have its own benchmark suite.
+
+```bash
+# Benchmark only distance metrics
+cargo bench -p chroma-distance
+
+# Benchmark only blockstore operations
+cargo bench -p chroma-blockstore
+```
+
+### 4. Parallel Compilation
+Cargo can compile independent crates in parallel, improving build times.
+
+### 5. Smaller Binary Sizes
+Services can selectively include only the crates they need. For example, a specialized distance calculation service wouldn't need blockstore or index modules.
+
+### 6. Better IDE Support
+IDEs can provide more accurate code navigation and completion when module boundaries are explicit.
+
+### 7. Easier Onboarding
+New developers can understand the system architecture by examining the workspace structure and crate dependencies.
+
+## Migration Notes
+
+### Import Changes
+
+**Before (monolithic)**:
+```rust
+use crate::types::Collection;
+use crate::distance::DistanceFunction;
+use crate::blockstore::provider::BlockfileProvider;
+```
+
+**After (modular)**:
+```rust
+use chroma_types::Collection;
+use chroma_distance::DistanceFunction;
+use chroma_blockstore::provider::BlockfileProvider;
+```
+
+### Proto Types
+
+Protocol buffer types are now in a separate crate:
+
+**Before**:
+```rust
+mod chroma_proto {
+    tonic::include_proto!("chroma");
+}
+```
+
+**After**:
+```rust
+use chroma_proto;
+```
+
+### Error Handling
+
+Error types moved to chroma-types:
+```rust
+use chroma_types::{ChromaError, ErrorCodes};
+```
+
+## Build Instructions
+
+### Full Workspace
+```bash
+cargo build --workspace
+cargo test --workspace
+```
+
+### Individual Crates
+```bash
+cargo build -p chroma-distance
+cargo test -p chroma-types
+cargo bench -p chroma-blockstore
+```
+
+### Running Services
+```bash
+cargo run --bin query_service
+cargo run --bin compaction_service
+```
+
+## Future Improvements
+
+1. **Feature Flags**: Add feature flags to make certain dependencies optional
+2. **Separate Execution Crate**: Extract execution module from worker into chroma-execution
+3. **Cache Crate**: Move caching logic into chroma-cache
+4. **Config Crate**: Centralize configuration in chroma-config
+5. **Proto Versioning**: Support multiple proto versions for backwards compatibility
+
+## Testing Strategy
+
+### Unit Tests
+Each crate contains its own unit tests:
+```bash
+cargo test -p <crate-name>
+```
+
+### Integration Tests
+Integration tests remain in the worker crate:
+```bash
+cargo test -p worker
+```
+
+### Benchmarks
+Run benchmarks for performance-critical crates:
+```bash
+cargo bench -p chroma-distance
+cargo bench -p chroma-blockstore
+```
+
+## Documentation
+
+Generate documentation for all crates:
+```bash
+cargo doc --workspace --no-deps --open
+```
+
+This creates a unified documentation site showing all public APIs and their relationships.
